<subSubSection pageId="217" pageNumber="218" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="217.[151,1437,223,2014]" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,965,691,717]" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Arrowtooth Flounder</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[1022,1116,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.78" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="cm" value="97.8">97.8 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1135,1219,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.779" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="in" value="38.5">38.5 in</quantity>
) FL (DFO); about 
<quantity box="[198,291,727,754]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.94" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="cm" value="99.4">99.4 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[308,391,727,754]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.9314" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="in" value="39.1">39.1 in</quantity>
) TL. Along with the 
<quantity box="[641,734,727,754]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.78" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="cm" value="97.8">97.8 cm</quantity>
fish in the DFO database, Maria Cornthwaite notes that fish as large as 
<quantity box="[326,411,763,790]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.03" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="cm" value="103.0">103 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[427,510,763,790]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.03124" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="in" value="40.6">40.6 in</quantity>
) FL (about 
<quantity box="[647,741,763,789]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.66192" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="in" value="104.8">104.8 in</quantity>
TL) have been reported in the British Columbia commercial fishery. Commander Islands and east coast of Kamchatka, to Cape Navarin, Bering Sea (northward to south of Saint Lawrence Island, 
<geoCoordinate box="[461,560,835,861]" degrees="62" direction="north" minutes="08" orientation="latitude" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" precision="925" value="62.133335">62°08’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[571,689,835,861]" degrees="170" direction="west" minutes="18" orientation="longitude" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" precision="925" value="-170.3">170°18’W</geoCoordinate>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Mecklenburg" box="[712,990,835,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Mecklenburg" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" pagination="109 - 140" refId="ref300975" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W., Moller, P. R. &amp; Steinke, D. (2011) Biodiversity of arctic marine fishes: taxonomy and zoogeography. Marine Biodiversity, 41, 109 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 010 - 0070 - z" type="journal article" year="2011">
Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[869,925,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), to Aleutian Islands and Gulf of Alaska (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[365,423,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2002), to Todos Santos (
<geoCoordinate box="[712,833,871,897]" degrees="23" direction="north" minutes="24.6" orientation="latitude" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" precision="92" value="23.41">23°24.6’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[846,986,871,897]" degrees="110" direction="west" minutes="13.8" orientation="longitude" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" precision="92" value="-110.23">110°13.8’W</geoCoordinate>
), southern Baja California (John Snow, pers. comm. to M.L.). Benthic; depth: 
<quantity box="[634,755,907,934]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.975" metricValueMax="11.86" metricValueMin="0.09" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="m" value="597.5" valueMax="1186.0" valueMin="9.0">9–1,186 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[770,904,907,934]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.972556" metricValueMax="11.85672" metricValueMin="0.088392" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" unit="ft" value="1959.5" valueMax="3890.0" valueMin="29.0">29–3,890 ft</quantity>
) (min.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Levings" box="[994,1151,907,933]" firstAuthor="Levings" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" refId="ref295518" refString="Levings, C. D. (1973) Sediments and abundance of Lycodopsis pacifica (Pisces, Zoarcidae) near Point Grey, B. C., with catch data for associated demersal fish. Fisheries Research Board of Canada Technical Report, 393." type="book" year="1973">Levings 1973</bibRefCitation>
; max.: NWFSC-FRAM). Records from the Chukchi Sea are in error (
<bibRefCitation author="Mecklenburg and Steinke" box="[668,1013,943,970]" firstAuthor="Mecklenburg" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" pagination="158 - 189" refId="ref300828" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W. &amp; Steinke, D. (2015) Ichthyofaunal baselines in the Pacific Arctic region and the RUSALCA study area. Oceanography, 28, 158 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.5670 / oceanog. 2015.64" type="journal article" year="2015">Mecklenburg and Steinke 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
